# pyFormex 0.5 known bugs    ( best viewed with emacs  -*- outline -*- )

KNOWN BUGS:

* With the mouse dolly zoom function (vertical mouse movement zooming), you can not move the camera beyond beyond the center of the displayed scene. 
  You can do it using the toolbar buttons or menus, and you can use mouse lens zooming (horizontal movement) to view further.

* Mouse zooming does not work correctly in projective mode.

* Mouse zooming can make a jump after a flyAlong().



If you find any bugs or malfunctions in pyFormex, please submit them to
http://developer.berlios.de/bugs/?group_id=2717

